page.title: 20HOUSING - N. LEEDS
page.content: The northern boundary of D block encloses one of the most affluent areas of the city.Wigton Lane contains large,detached houses upto 25 yrs old. High Ash estate to the south of Wigton Lane is more recent and houses "young executives".Sandhill Oval and adjoining streets consist of pre 1939 semi and detached houses formerly occupied mainly Jewish business men In contrast,Street Lane,a middle class area,has changed in recent years as the Asian community has increased.Bordering the northern edge of Moortown Ring Road are a variety of council properties,some of the 1945 era, others built within the last 10 yrs. SCHOOLS TAKING PART IN THE D BLOCK: ST.ANDREW'S MIDDLE,BRODETSKY PRIMARY, ST.PAUL'S PRIMARY,TALBOT ROAD PRIMARY.
